# unstableToast

## Import

```jsx live=false
import { unstableToast } from '@node-real/bee';
```

## Usage

<UnstableToast />

```jsx live=false
<Wrap>
  <Button
    onClick={() => {
      unstableToast({
        title: 'Success message title',
        description: 'Unable to create user account.',
        status: 'success',
        isClosable: false,
      });
    }}
  >
    success
  </Button>

  <Button
    onClick={() => {
      unstableToast({
        title: 'Danger message title',
        description: 'Unable to create user account.',
        status: 'danger',
      });
    }}
  >
    danger
  </Button>

  <Button
    onClick={() => {
      unstableToast({
        title: 'Warning message title',
        description: 'Unable to create user account.',
        status: 'warning',
      });
    }}
  >
    warning
  </Button>
</Wrap>
```

## Close toast manually

Each call of `unstableToast` will return an `id`, you can close the specified toast by taking this id as the parameter of `unstableToast.close()`, or you can close all toasts by `unstableToast.closeAll()`

```jsx live=false
const id = unstableToast({
  title: 'Warning message title',
  description: 'Unable to create user account.',
  status: 'warning',
});

unstableToast.close(id);

unstableToast.closeAll();
```

